---
layout: base.njk
title: Web Everything - Home
---

{% from "display-toolbar.njk" import displayToolbar %}

<section class="intro">
    <h1>Web Everything</h1>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 2rem;">
        <strong>Protocol over Implementation.</strong><br>
        Defining the missing standards for the modern web, bridging the gap between frameworks and enable true interoperability.
    </p>
    <a href="/mission/" style="color: var(--color-primary); font-weight: 600; text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid var(--color-primary); display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.5rem;">
        Read the Manifesto
        <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M5 12h14"/><path d="m12 5 7 7-7 7"/></svg>
    </a>
    <p style="margin-top: 2rem; font-size: 1rem; color: var(--color-text-muted);">
        See the protocols in action with
        <a href="{{ links.frontierUrl }}" style="color: var(--color-primary);" target="_blank" rel="noopener">FrontierUI</a>,
        a reference implementation. Build your own &mdash; the protocols are open for anyone to implement.
    </p>
</section>

<section class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="section-title">Standards</h2>
    <div class="section-head">
        <p class="section-desc">Low-level specifications expanding the capabilities of the platform.</p>
        {{ displayToolbar("standards") }}
    </div>
    {# #2019 (keystone #2016): the landing grid is SSR'd from our `we-card` at BUILD TIME. `weProjectGrid`
       shells out to the pinned FUI build-CLI (render-from-data per #2007) and returns the whole grid as real
       `<article class="fui-card">` / `<span class="fui-badge…">` HTML — correct with JS off, view-source-
       visible. The transient `<we-card>`/`<we-badge>` client upgrade (base.njk) becomes a pure enhancement
       (the SSR page carries the finished native element, no `<we-*>` wrapper, so nothing to re-upgrade). #}
    {% set standardProjects = [] %}
    {% for project in projects %}
      {% if project.category == 'standard' %}
        {% set standardProjects = (standardProjects.push(project), standardProjects) %}
      {% endif %}
    {% endfor %}
    {% weProjectGrid standardProjects %}
</section>

<section>
    <h2 class="section-title">Application Protocols</h2>
    <div class="section-head">
        <p class="section-desc">High-level standards for architecture, interoperability, and application design.</p>
        {{ displayToolbar("protocols") }}
    </div>
    {% set protocolProjects = [] %}
    {% for project in projects %}
      {% if project.category == 'utility' or project.category == 'ecosystem' %}
        {% set protocolProjects = (protocolProjects.push(project), protocolProjects) %}
      {% endif %}
    {% endfor %}
    {% weProjectGrid protocolProjects %}
</section>

<section style="margin-top: 3rem;">
    <h2 class="section-title">Implementations &amp; Tools</h2>
    <p class="section-desc">Projects that bring Web Everything protocols to life, and the platforms built on top of them. Building your own? The protocols are open for anyone to implement.</p>
    {# The impls tiles are not in the `projects` data (they link out to external sites), so we compose an
       inline list carrying each tile's `url`; `external: true` links them out with target=_blank. #}
    {% set implProjects = [
        { name: "FrontierUI", status: "active", isSvg: true, icon: "/assets/icons/frontierui.svg", url: links.frontierUrl,
          description: "A reference implementation of Web Everything protocols. Conforming building blocks for state management, routing, views, tabs, and more." },
        { name: "Plateau", status: "poc", isSvg: true, icon: "/assets/icons/plateau.svg", url: links.plateauUrl,
          description: "An enterprise front-end platform management product, built natively on Web Everything. Catalogs applications, libraries, and standards across an organization, and ships configurator tools assembled entirely from the protocols." }
    ] %}
    {% weProjectGrid implProjects, { external: true, gridClass: "project-grid project-grid--centered" } %}
</section>

<section class="creator-section">
    <h2>About the Creator</h2>
    <p>
        <a href="https://chalbert.github.io/portfolio" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><strong>Nicolas Gilbert</strong></a> is a passionate frontend developer and consultant based in Quebec, Canada.
        Specializing in modern web applications, Web Components, and developer experience tools.
    </p>
    <div class="creator-links">
        <a href="https://chalbert.github.io/portfolio/contact/" class="creator-link">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" style="margin-right: 8px;"><rect width="20" height="14" x="2" y="7" rx="2" ry="2"/><path d="M16 21V5a2 2 0 0 0-2-2h-4a2 2 0 0 0-2 2v16"/></svg>
            Work with me
        </a>
        <a href="https://patreon.com/" class="creator-link">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" style="margin-right: 8px;"><path d="M19 14c1.49-1.46 3-3.21 3-5.5A5.5 5.5 0 0 0 16.5 3c-1.76 0-3 .5-4.5 2-1.5-1.5-2.74-2-4.5-2A5.5 5.5 0 0 0 2 8.5c0 2.3 1.5 4.05 3 5.5l7 7Z"/></svg>
            Support this project
        </a>
    </div>
</section>

<script src="/assets/js/home-display.js"></script>
